{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c1dfea29-32b3-4021-86a3-0fa4be6a9168","content":"You're on MSTest 3.8.2 which supports constructor injection for `TestContext`. Here's the recommended pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n    private MyService _service;\n\n    // Constructor injection for TestContext (MSTest v3+)\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n        // Synchronous initialization here\n    }\n\n    // Async initialization (runs before each test)\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        _service = await MyService.CreateAsync();\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void ExampleTest()\n    {\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Running test...\");\n        Assert.IsNotNull(_service);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- **Constructor** — use for synchronous setup and receiving `TestContext` via injection (no property needed)\n- **`[TestInitialize]`** — use for async setup (`async Task` return type); runs before each test\n- **`[ClassInitialize]`** — for one-time async setup shared across all tests in the class (static method)\n\nThis replaces the older `public TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` property pattern with cleaner constructor injection.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cfdfbceb-897b-4487-82e4-294d6aecb049","outputTokens":318,"requestId":"E3C5:1ED62C:17A99F6:1A8C8E8:6A05284F"},"id":"2d55b4fa-41ee-4990-85ce-0a0b2100f8da","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:41:43.184Z","parentId":"220f9ce8-d510-44a0-af3c-5c0742a50972"}
